.TH "dax_direct_access" 9 "dax_direct_access" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dax_direct_access \- translate a device pgoff to an absolute pfn
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" dax_direct_access
.BI "(struct dax_device *dax_dev "  ","
.BI "pgoff_t pgoff "  ","
.BI "long nr_pages "  ","
.BI "void **kaddr "  ","
.BI "pfn_t *pfn "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dax_dev" 12
a dax_device instance representing the logical memory range
.IP "pgoff" 12
offset in pages from the start of the device to translate
.IP "nr_pages" 12
number of consecutive pages caller can handle relative to \fIpfn\fP
.IP "kaddr" 12
output parameter that returns a virtual address mapping of pfn
.IP "pfn" 12
output parameter that returns an absolute pfn translation of \fIpgoff\fP
.SH "RETURN"
negative errno if an error occurs, otherwise the number of
pages accessible at the device relative \fIpgoff\fP.
